More Information 

Apple works to protect Sign in with Apple at Work & School with strong authentication — powered by Touch ID, Face ID, Optic ID, and strong passcode options.

Apple may receive anonymous and aggregate information about Sign in with Apple at Work & School, including non-personal data about the use of Sign in with Apple at Work & School. Apple may use this information to improve related Apple products and services, and for fraud prevention and security purposes. Apple will not attempt to reidentify any anonymous or aggregated Sign in with Apple data we receive.

